@startuml
title QueryEngine State Carry-Over - What Survives Between Turns

skinparam backgroundColor #FEFEFE
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam dpi 130
skinparam defaultFontName Georgia
skinparam defaultFontSize 14
skinparam TitleFontSize 19
skinparam TitleFontColor #161616
skinparam NoteFontSize 12
skinparam ArrowFontSize 12
skinparam ArrowColor #5E5A53
skinparam state {
  BackgroundColor #F2E9D9
  BorderColor #1D1D1D
  FontColor #161616
  ArrowColor #5E5A53
  StartColor #8C2721
  EndColor #161616
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #F5EBDD
  BorderColor #8C2721
  FontColor #7B1E1E
}

state "<b>Conversation Shell</b>\nmutableMessages\nreadFileState cache\nabortController\npermission denials\nusage accounting\nmemory / skill indexes" as Shell #E8DDD0

state "Turn N" as T1 #EFE6D8 {
  state "inner loop" as I1
}
state "Turn N+1" as T2 #EFE6D8 {
  state "inner loop" as I2
}
state "Turn N+2" as T3 #EFE6D8 {
  state "inner loop" as I3
}

[*] --> T1
T1 --> T2 : next turn
T2 --> T3 : next turn
T3 --> [*]

Shell --> T1 : read / write
Shell --> T2 : read / write
Shell --> T3 : read / write

note right of Shell
  Each turn reads and mutates
  the same shell. Continuity
  lives here, not inside any
  single inner loop.
end note

note bottom of T2
  A turn is one pass through
  the inner loop. The shell
  is what makes turn N+1
  different from turn N.
end note

@enduml
